                'banner_image' => 'storage/practice_areas/police_misconduct_banner.webp',
                'content_image' => 'storage/practice_areas/police_misconduct.webp',
                'short_description' => '<div><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 33px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgba(249, 248, 246, 0.48); color: rgb(109, 109, 109); font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Have your civil rights been violated? Are you a victim of police misconduct? Wrongful arrests and excessive force are forms of police brutality as well as unjustified police shootings.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 33px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgba(249, 248, 246, 0.48); color: rgb(109, 109, 109); font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">At the Cochran Firm, we specialize in helping victims of police misconduct in Los Angeles. Our police misconduct lawyers represent victims whose constitutional rights have been violated, and no firm in California has more success in pursuing justice for victims of police misconduct and civil rights violations.</p></div>',
                'description' => '<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_2 et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light et_multi_view__hover_selector" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 29.6719px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: center center / cover no-repeat rgba(249, 248, 246, 0.48); overflow-wrap: break-word; text-align: left; animation-timing-function: linear; animation-duration: 200ms; font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><div class="et_pb_text_inner" data-et-multi-view="{&quot;schema&quot;:{&quot;content&quot;:{&quot;desktop&quot;:&quot;<div class=\&quot;page-header\&quot;><\/div>\n<h2><b>Understanding Your Civil Rights<\/b><\/h2>\n<p>The civil rights granted by the United States Constitution come primarily from the following:<\/p>\n<ul class=\&quot;timeline-list\&quot;>\n<li><b>The Fourth Amendment<\/b>: Protects you against\u00a0illegal searches and seizures\u00a0and<span>\u00a0<\/span>police brutality. We have been successful in handling these civil rights cases, as well as\u00a0unlawful arrest\u00a0and\u00a0wrongful conviction<span>\u00a0<\/span>cases, which often involve violations of the Fifth and Fourteenth Amendment\u2019s \u201cdue process of law\u201d clauses.\n<\/li>\n<li><b>The First Amendment<\/b>: Guarantees freedom of speech and provides protection against retaliation. This is especially applicable to whistleblower cases\u2014also known as a qui tam lawsuit.\n<\/li>\n<li><b>The Civil Rights Act of 1964:<\/b>\u00a0Prohibits federal and state governments and employers from discrimination based on race, color, religion, sex or national origin. This is often referenced in employment law cases.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><b>Types of Police Misconduct\/Civil Rights Violations<\/b><\/h2>\n<p>The Cochran Firm has a team of police misconduct attorneys who are committed to helping you secure damages for civil rights violations. We have expertise in litigating civil rights cases involving all forms of misconduct and fraud by police and prosecutors, including:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Wrongful Convictions<\/li>\n<li>Police Shootings<\/li>\n<li>Police Brutality<\/li>\n<li>Unlawful Arrests<\/li>\n<li>Unlawful Searches and Seizures<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>&quot;,&quot;tablet&quot;:&quot;<p style=\&quot;text-align: justify;\&quot;>Trial Lawyers for the People.....<\/p>\n<p style=\&quot;text-align: justify;\&quot;>When we get involved, we seek economic justice, and will make every effort to make this a better and safer world through your case.<\/p>\n<p style=\&quot;text-align: justify;\&quot;>First comes the phone call. Or e-mail. Or you just stop by our Firm, the same Firm Johnnie L. Cochran, Jr. made history from for several decades. You speak with one of our highly trained legal assistants, we take down the information, and it is evaluated and summarized by our intake department.<\/p>\n<p style=\&quot;text-align: justify;\&quot;>The intake personnel directly discuss your case with one of our lawyers, often one of our partners, as quickly as possible. Shortly thereafter, you\u2019re meeting with a Cochran Firm lawyer, a Trial Lawyer for the People like you, and discussing the beginning of a legal relationship. Here\u2019s what you can expect.<\/p>\n<p style=\&quot;text-align: justify;\&quot;>First, our commitment. We are excellent in the fields we practice. Whether it be civil rights, employment law, discrimination, negligence, medical malpractice, product liability, government road design, insurance bad faith, complex medical injury or death, we bring decades of skills and accomplishments to the relationship. What we offer to you is our collective passion, intellect, and legal power. And we do this for you on a contingency fee. If we don\u2019t win, you don\u2019t pay us. We advance all costs. We are there for you, guiding you through the legal process.<\/p>\n<p style=\&quot;text-align: justify;\&quot;>The family approach of the Cochran Firm is seen throughout our work. From the friendliness of our receptionists, to the intake department, then to the team of lawyers and legal specialists working for you, we bring a personal and hands-on approach to our task. Economic justice. Changing the world, one case at a time. As Johnnie used to say, everybody from the O\u2019Jays to the No Jays\u2026.<\/p>&quot;,&quot;phone&quot;:&quot;<div class=\&quot;page-header\&quot;><\/div>\n<h2><b>A Quick Look at Your Civil Rights<\/b><\/h2>\n<p>The civil rights granted by the United States Constitution come primarily from the following:<\/p>\n<ul class=\&quot;timeline-list\&quot;>\n<li><b>The Fourth Amendment<\/b>: Protects you against illegal searches and seizures and<span> <\/span>police brutality. We have been successful in handling these civil rights cases, as well as unlawful arrest and wrongful conviction<span> <\/span>cases, which often involve violations of the Fifth and Fourteenth Amendment\u2019s \u201cdue process of law\u201d clauses.<\/li>\n<li><b>The First Amendment<\/b>: Guarantees freedom of speech and provides protection against retaliation. This is especially applicable to whistleblower cases\u2014also known as a qui tam lawsuit.<\/li>\n<li><b>The Civil Rights Act of 1964:<\/b> Prohibits federal and state governments and employers from discrimination based on race, color, religion, sex or national origin. This is often referenced in employment law cases.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><b>Types of Police Misconduct\/Civil Rights Violations<\/b><\/h2>\n<p>The Cochran Firm Los Angeles has police misconduct attorneys who are committed to helping you secure damages for civil rights violations. We have expertise in litigating civil rights cases involving all forms of misconduct and fraud by police and prosecutors, including:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Wrongful Convictions<\/li>\n<li>Police Shootings<\/li>\n<li>Police Brutality<\/li>\n<li>Unlawful Arrests<\/li>\n<li>Unlawful Searches and Seizures<\/li>\n<\/ul>&quot;}},&quot;slug&quot;:&quot;et_pb_text&quot;}" data-et-multi-view-load-tablet-hidden="true" data-et-multi-view-load-phone-hidden="true" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;"><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 26px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1em; font-weight: 500;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 26px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">Understanding Your Civil Rights</strong></h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 33px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">The civil rights granted by the United States Constitution come primarily from the following:</p><ul class="timeline-list" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 33px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; list-style: disc; line-height: 26px;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; text-align: left;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">The Fourth Amendment</strong>: Protects you against&nbsp;illegal searches and seizures&nbsp;and<span style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">&nbsp;</span>police brutality. We have been successful in handling these civil rights cases, as well as&nbsp;unlawful arrest&nbsp;and&nbsp;wrongful conviction<span style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">&nbsp;</span>cases, which often involve violations of the Fifth and Fourteenth Amendment’s “due process of law” clauses.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; text-align: left;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">The First Amendment</strong>: Guarantees freedom of speech and provides protection against retaliation. This is especially applicable to whistleblower cases—also known as a qui tam lawsuit.</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; text-align: left;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">The Civil Rights Act of 1964:</strong>&nbsp;Prohibits federal and state governments and employers from discrimination based on race, color, religion, sex or national origin. This is often referenced in employment law cases.</li></ul><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 33px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">&nbsp;<br></p><h2 style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 26px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1em; font-weight: 500;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 26px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">Types of Police Misconduct/Civil Rights Violations</strong></h2><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 33px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">The Cochran Firm has a team of police misconduct attorneys who are committed to helping you secure damages for civil rights violations. We have expertise in litigating civil rights cases involving all forms of misconduct and fraud by police and prosecutors, including:</p><ul style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 10px 33px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; list-style: disc; line-height: 26px;"><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; text-align: left;">Wrongful Convictions</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; text-align: left;">Police Shootings</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; text-align: left;">Police Brutality</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; text-align: left;">Unlawful Arrests</li><li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; text-align: left;">Unlawful Searches and Seizures</li></ul><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;">&nbsp;<br></p></div></div><div class="et_pb_button_module_wrapper et_pb_button_1_wrapper  et_pb_module " style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: center center / cover no-repeat rgba(249, 248, 246, 0.48); animation-timing-function: linear; animation-duration: 200ms; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><a class="et_pb_button et_pb_button_1 et_pb_bg_layout_light" href="sms:+18336763254" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.3em 1em; border: 2px solid rgb(158, 125, 50); outline: 0px; font-size: 17px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: center center / cover no-repeat tra